        <p> Today has now decided where I will spend my 30th birthday. I will be removed as far as possible. With a rather high probability in or near the city of Christchurch. I will also not celebrate alone with a rather high probability, but with Sam. But I will only tell her where I am exactly that day when she promises that I don't have to sweep. By the way, Christchurch is located on the South Island of New Zealand. </p>
        <p> Why now? Very easy. According to Wikipedia, New Zealand is the most distant place. But it is even easier. I fly from Christchurch to Sydney the next afternoon. I have finally booked my flights and only wait for the confirmation of Qantas that everything is confirmed. </p>
        <p> Since my company still could not begin to decide after 7 months whether a break on the basis of unpaid vacation would be possible, I have now decided to book and plan the long tour. So I will now fly in Hamburg on October 9th, 2012 in the evening. I have now put my return on 23/24/2013. Since my international driver's license is going on on this date and I am back in Germany in time for my brother's 35th birthday. </p>
